AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Bye for now. &gt;&gt; All right, let\'s jump right in. I want to keep it brief, but I also want to share where my head\'s been at with AI recently. &gt;&gt; We have a problem. &gt;&gt; For the people who care, I\'ll keep it at 2x speed. If you\'re new and want to get'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to the good stuff, just click somewhere around here. Is AI filmmaking? &gt;&gt; Is it taking over Hollywood? Will it replace the movie industry forever? Let\'s be real honest here. They said this when animation came out, when CGI came out, and it\'s just not true.'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Remember, we\'re talking about AI video generation in 2026. All right, Higgsfield just premiered their full 80-minute-long motion picture film at Cannes Festival. Influencers in the real filmmaking industry are getting ripped to shreds for sharing their honest feedback and opinions on it. Directors,'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'producers scared to admit their level of excitement. &gt;&gt; But you know the easiest thing to do about all of this is simply to just say, "AI." &gt;&gt; And get on with it. You don\'t have talent. You\'ll never amount to anything if you use AI. Slop is slop. I\'d be'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lying if I said those comments did nothing to me because I\'m only human, but [music] we\'re moving forward. AI is here, and AI is here to stay, and we have to adapt. &gt;&gt; I think my only piece of I won\'t say advice, but nuggets, if you will, when we\'re faced with these probing questions'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'about whether or not AI is art, I said this in my last video, and I\'ll say it again because this is what I stand by. AI, if used correctly, is the most powerful paintbrush that we can have in our creative toolkit. It\'s not to'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'replace tools, and it\'s definitely not to replace [music] people. AI is only as good as the people behind it. Keep AI as a complementary brush in your toolkit, but don\'t forget that you need the skills to use them correctly. Lean on'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'other creators to help you. Take your time, learn, grow, evolve. If I had AI 10-15 years ago, I wouldn\'t have known how an actual camera operates, how to light a room instead of lighting the'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'subject, how to use things like atmosphere, haze, and things that I\'ve baked into the skills that we\'re using now to build these cool videos. I say this to say, if you\'re getting into AI, you\'re discovering how cool AI videos'

[02:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can be. I\'m also asking you to [music] respect the craft of the film industry as a whole. Take time to understand and learn from some of the greats just as I have, and I really believe that once we start doing that, we\'ve got a background'

[02:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in it, we\'ll really be able to lean on each other and build something amazing. [music] So, now that I\'m done rapping, let\'s start with the upscaling, shall we? We\'re using Topaz for this. It\'s not a sponsor. Topaz didn\'t reach out to me, Topaz. But, let\'s get into it. So, I\'ve'

[02:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'got a clip here that we\'re working on. I put this together really quick just to show the video process. We\'re using 720p just cuz I don\'t want to be spending so much credits. This is 16x9 footage.'

[03:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We\'re also going to talk about what it looks like to upscale 21x9 footage as that [music] is very different, and it\'s got a little bit of a different codec settings. So, we\'re going to go over here, and we\'re going to come to enhancement. First off, it\'s going to'

[03:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'drop you in the Starlight precise model, which is good, but it takes forever. So, we\'re not going to be [music] working with that right now. What I\'m going to be using is Iris. It\'s a much better specialized [music] enhancement for'

[03:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'faces. Proteus is also another good model to be using, but I think Iris is the best one for now. We\'re going to come up here to output resolution, and we\'re going to drop it down to 3840 by 2160 cuz I love 4K. We\'re also going to add noise here. This is digital noise,'

[03:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and this is different from film grain. We\'re not going to be putting grain into our upscale video here. Although it does look good, it\'s just going to take a lot longer to render. If you don\'t have any grain overlays, that\'s what I use in my'

[03:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'videos. That\'s something that you can get somewhere. I\'m sure you can find for free. If you don\'t have those though and you don\'t mind spending the extra time [music] to render, I would throw grain in here. I\'ll show you the settings later, but we\'re going to add noise'

[04:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here. Just two or three, nothing crazy. Recover detail is what makes it a lot sharper and like I said in my last video, we don\'t want really sharp cinematic images. Focus fix, [music] we\'re going to leave that off because we\'re working with video generation.'

[04:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Nothing is out of focus. So, if I were to use grain, I would set it to gray. I would set the grain amount to somewhere around 70 and 80. I would set the grain size down to like 1.5, 1.8, something [music] nice and small. And then we\'ll'

[04:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'keep the grain density where it is. Input condition is low quality and we\'re going to use advanced automatic tuning. We\'re going to come over here to the codec settings and we\'re just going to keep it at H.264. You can do Apple [music] ProRes, but that doesn\'t make'

[04:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'any sense because we\'re only using video generation. ProRes would be if we were going to be heavy [music] color grading and things like that, but again, we\'re just using AI video generation. So, [music] no need to do that until we get'

[04:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it to some kind of AI video that we can start using 10-bit color and log and all that color profile, but I don\'t know when we\'ll be able to get there. Leave everything else as is. Dynamic bit rate. If we\'re going to be upscaling 21x9'

[05:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'footage, this is what this is going to look like and this is a small clip of something that we\'re working on right now. Super secret stuff. Don\'t show anyone. &gt;&gt; Okay. &gt;&gt; 21x9 is different because it is a different size, obviously. We\'re going'

[05:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to use a custom resolution setting that [music] is going to be 5040 by 2160. That is going to be our 4K settings for 21x9. We\'re going to keep all of the rest of the settings the same, but in our codec settings, we\'re going to'

[05:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'change the bit rate from dynamic to constant and we\'re going to leave that at 24. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; And that is pretty much it for the upscale settings. Now, once you drop this into your 4K timeline, add some grain, do a little bit of color'

[05:46] [scene:talk]
